canonical_structure.name: UBX-LOG-CREATE
canonical_structure.description: Create log file and activate the logging subsystem.

bits.name: circular
bits.description: Log is circular (new entries overwrite old ones in a full log) if this bit set

fields.name: logSize
fields.description: Indicates the size of the log: 0 (maximum safe size), 1 (minimum size), 2 (user-defined)

fields.name: userDefinedSize
fields.description: Sets the maximum amount of space in the filestore that can be used by the logging task. This field is only applicable if logSize is set to user-defined.

issues: Failed to identify message fields, labeling the entire 8-byte payload as reserved.
Fields list is empty despite fixed length of 8 bytes.
Field at offset 2 named 'reserved1' instead of 'reserved0', which is a minor naming convention difference.
Field at offset 4 named 'userDefined' instead of 'userDefinedSize'.

adjudication.reasoning: The UBX-LOG-CREATE message is highly stable across multiple u-blox generations (M8, M9, M10, and F9 series). It consistently uses an 8-byte payload containing a version, a bitfield, a reserved byte, a size-mode selector, and a 4-byte custom size field. Extractions 2 and 7 were identified as errors because they failed to parse the field-level detail that is clearly present in all other sources. Minor differences in field naming (e.g., 'reserved1' vs 'reserved0' or 'userDefined' vs 'userDefinedSize') do not represent protocol variations but rather minor documentation or extraction labeling choices.
